cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.TL, cs.SE, cs.FL 

This paper deals with the design and metatheory of a gradual language with explicit parametric polymorphism, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the preservation of relational parametricity, which is a topic in logic and verification (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper explores the use of Abstracting Gradual Typing methodology, which is a technique used in type systems (cs.TL). The paper also discusses the challenges in designing a gradual language and the semantic issues that arise, which are topics in software engineering (cs.SE) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
